headline: Walmart's Mexico subsidiary plans to appeal a $4.6 million fine for alleged monopolistic practices
summary: Walmart’s Mexico subsidiary said Friday it plans to appeal a $4.6 million fine for alleged anti-competitive practices involving suppliers.  Walmart de Mexico said in a statement that it had talked with suppliers to see if there were any concerns.  The agency that issued the fine, known as the Federal Competition Commission, expressed concerns about a “relative monopolistic practice.”
